    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Vigna retusa are its anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antioxidant activities. The bioactive compounds responsible for these properties include flavonoids, such as kaempferol and quercetin, which are known to exhibit anti-inflammatory activity by inhibiting the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines. Additionally, the plant's antimicrobial properties are attributed to the presence of saponins, which have been shown to exhibit antibacterial and antifungal activities by disrupting cell membrane integrity and inhibiting the synthesis of ergosterol. Vigna retusa's antioxidant properties are also attributed to the presence of volatile oils, such as limonene and pinene, which have been shown to scavenge free radicals and reduce oxidative stress. Furthermore, the plant's ability to reduce inflammation and oxidative stress makes it a potential candidate for the treatment of various diseases, including diabetes and cardiovascular disease.",
